<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/normalize.css@8.0.1/normalize.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/@twilio-paste/design-tokens@6.3.0/dist/tokens.custom-properties.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="index.css" />
  <title>Twiliomatic</title>
  <!-- Global site tag (gtag.js) - Google Analytics -->
  <script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=UA-178595660-1"></script>
  <script>
    window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
    function gtag() { dataLayer.push(arguments); }
    gtag('js', new Date());

    gtag('config', 'UA-178595660-1');
  </script>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="tp-app" id="app">
    <header class="tp-site-header">
      <img src="twiliomatic_type_v2_logo.png" alt="" width="550" class="robot-image" />
    </header>
    <main class="tp-site-main">
      <div class="tp-site-main-inner">
        <div class="tp-layout tp-layout--2-col">
          <div class="tp-layout-col">
            <!-- checkout Paste Headings https://paste.twilio.design/components/heading -->
            <h1>You missed us at <a href="https://signal.twilio.com/">SIGNAL</a>!</h1>
            <p class="tp-lead">
              We used our bot to generate <a
                href="https://www.twilio.com/docs/glossary/what-is-twilio-markup-language-twiml#how-does-twiml-work"
                target="_blank">TwiML</a> for use in Twilio apps.
            </p>
            <hr />
            <p>This application makes use of <a href="https://openai.com/">Open AI's API</a> and GPT-3 to
              generate <a
                href="https://www.twilio.com/docs/glossary/what-is-twilio-markup-language-twiml#how-does-twiml-work">TwiML</a>
              for use in Twilio apps. It also uses Microsoft Azure's Cognitive services for content moderation. It runs
              completely
              on <a href="https://twilio.com/runtime">Twilio's Runtime platform</a>. Check out the code on <a
                href="https://github.com/TwilioDevEd/Twiliomatic">GitHub</a> if you
              would like to spin up your own instance and learn more.

            <p><a href="https://gist.github.com/Twiliomatic">View the code generated by attendees during the
                Keynote.</a></p>
          </div>
          <div class="tp-layout-col">
            <h1>Deploy our favorites.</h1>
            {{#each favorites}}
            <h3>{{ this.query }}</h3>
            <div class="tp-gist">
              <script src="https://gist.github.com/{{ GITHUB_USER }}/{{ this.gistId }}.js"></script>
            </div>
            <a href="/results?GistId={{ this.gistId }}">Deploy this app!</a>
            {{/each}}
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- <img src="robot.png" alt="" width="550" class="robot-image" /> -->
    </main>

    <footer class="tp-site-footer">
      <div class="tp-footer-credit">
        Built with
        <a class="tp-footer-link" href="https://paste.twilio.design" target="_blank">Paste</a> | <a
          href="https://www.twilio.com/legal/aup">Twilio's Acceptable Use Policy</a>
      </div>
    </footer>
    <style>
      #forkongithub a {
        background: #F22F46;
        color: #fff;
        text-decoration: none;
        font-family: arial, sans-serif;
        text-align: center;
        font-weight: bold;
        padding: 5px 40px;
        font-size: 1rem;
        line-height: 2rem;
        position: relative;
        transition: 0.5s;
      }

      #forkongithub a:hover {
        background: #001489;
        color: #fff;
      }

      #forkongithub a::before,
      #forkongithub a::after {
        content: "";
        width: 100%;
        display: block;
        position: absolute;
        top: 1px;
        left: 0;
        height: 1px;
        background: #fff;
      }

      #forkongithub a::after {
        bottom: 1px;
        top: auto;
      }

      @media screen and (min-width:800px) {
        #forkongithub {
          position: fixed;
          display: block;
          top: 0;
          right: 0;
          width: 200px;
          overflow: hidden;
          height: 200px;
          z-index: 9999;
        }

        #forkongithub a {
          width: 200px;
          position: absolute;
          top: 60px;
          right: -60px;
          transform: rotate(45deg);
          -webkit-transform: rotate(45deg);
          -ms-transform: rotate(45deg);
          -moz-transform: rotate(45deg);
          -o-transform: rotate(45deg);
          box-shadow: 4px 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
        }
      }
    </style><span id="forkongithub"><a href="https://github.com/TwilioDevEd/Twiliomatic">Fork me on
        GitHub</a></span>
    <script src="index.js"></script>
  </div>
  <script src="index.js"></script>
</body>

</html>